 = 90{\\deg}), a 20% increase of the\nbolometric albedo is observed near perihelion. Heliocentric variations of the\ndust color are not significant in the analyzed time period. Measured color\ntemperatures are varying from 260 to 320 K, and follow a r^0.6 variation in the\nr_h = 1.24-1.5 AU range, close to the expected r_h^0.5 value.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Jan 2019 09:39:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
